		<h1>Lit Hub Daily: May 1, 2026</h1>
		<h2>THE BEST OF THE LITERARY INTERNET</h2>	</div>
			<div class="featured-img-container">
			<img class="story-img" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/fscottmayday.jpg" title="Lit Hub Daily: May 1, 2026">
								</div>
	</div>
									<div class="story-body">
								<span class="caption"> TODAY: In 1919, the May Day Riots take place in Cleveland, Ohio<span style="font-weight: 400">. They will become the subject of F. Scott Fitzgerald’s short story “May Day,” first published in <i>The Smart Set</i> in 1920<i><b>. </b></i></span><span style="font-weight: 400"> </span></span>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://lithub.com/satire-isnt-dead-we-just-misunderstand-it/">Is satire really dead?</a> According to Erin Van Der Meer, we’re the ones who just aren’t getting it. | Lit Hub <a href="https://lithub.com/category/newsandculture/humor/">Humor</a></li>
<li>“I would never deny a witch her will.” Lauren Groff considers <a href="http://lithub.com/lauren-groff-there-is-no-such-thing-as-boredom-only-noticing">the radical act of doing nothing</a>. | Lit Hub <a href="https://lithub.com/category/craftandcriticism/craft-and-advice/">Craft</a></li>
<li>Caroline Carlson recommends <a href="https://lithub.com/10-great-new-childrens-books-out-in-may-2026/">10 great children’s books coming in May</a> by Christian Robinson, Stephen Barr, Lauren Wolk and more! | Lit Hub <a href="https://lithub.com/category/readinglists/">Reading Lists</a></li>
<li>Why our prehistoric ancestors <a href="https://lithub.com/on-humanitys-earliest-attempts-to-make-a-home/">were actually incredible architects</a>: “What began as simple returns to favored spots evolved into increasingly sophisticated and enduring manipulations of space that would ultimately distinguish us from every other species on Earth.” | Lit Hub <a href="https://lithub.com/category/newsandculture/history/">History</a></li>
<li>Rebecca Morgan Frank <a href="https://lithub.com/7-new-poetry-collections-to-read-this-may/">recommends 7 new poetry collections</a>, including work by Carolina Ebeid, Laura Kasischke, and Luis Muñoz. | Lit Hub <a href="https://lithub.com/category/readinglists/">Reading Lists</a></li>
<li>&#8220;Kim Kardashian has become ubiquitous, as if she were a very hot dictator whose portrait hung in every home in America.&#8221; <a href="https://0b74a5e2.streak-link.com/C3b1xgwERO-nwNcioQCeeCc7/https%3A%2F%2Fbookmarks.reviews%2F5-reviews-you-need-to-read-this-week-10%2F" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://0b74a5e2.streak-link.com/C3b1xgwERO-nwNcioQCeeCc7/https%253A%252F%252Fbookmarks.reviews%252F5-reviews-you-need-to-read-this-week-10%252F&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1777661771586000&amp;usg=AOvVaw0QIqf3iisKVuZGDgEcdl5B" class="external">5 book reviews you need to read this week</a> | <a href="https://0b74a5e2.streak-link.com/C3b1xg08fIBIDUymgwea1cQ7/https%3A%2F%2Fbookmarks.reviews%2F" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://0b74a5e2.streak-link.com/C3b1xg08fIBIDUymgwea1cQ7/https%253A%252F%252Fbookmarks.reviews%252F&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1777661771586000&amp;usg=AOvVaw2HOPYSVDfb_XsrEkwBLuGM" class="external">Book Marks</a></li>
<li>These <a href="https://lithub.com/mays-best-sci-fi-and-fantasy-books-2/">upcoming sci-fi and fantasy books</a> will have you craving adventure in fantastical, futuristic worlds. | Lit Hub <a href="https://lithub.com/category/readinglists/">Reading Lists</a></li>
<li>“At some point I stopped stopping / to write, life a mark of living not clicking.” Read <a href="https://lithub.com/the-formal-beginnings-of-packing-a-poem-by-amanda-nadelberg/">“The Formal Beginnings of Packing,” a poem by Amanda Nadelberg</a> from the collection <em>Shake Until Cloudy</em>. | Lit Hub <a href="https://lithub.com/category/fictionandpoetry/poem/">Poetry</a></li>
<li>“We were at my cousin Channing’s house, in the woods of a New England town, when our grandfather told us the Korean story of Chunhyang and Mongryong.” Read from <a href="https://lithub.com/dreamt-i-found-you/"> Jimin Han’s new novel, <em>Dreamt I Found You</em></a>. | Lit Hub <a href="https://lithub.com/category/fictionandpoetry/from-the-novel/">Fiction</a></li>
<li>“When I do not reckon with the ways that casinos, betting apps, and late-stage capitalism operationalize my sadness, economic anxiety, and greed, I risk more privately and talk less about that risk publicly.”<a href="https://www.vanityfair.com/culture/story/kiese-laymon-casino-court" class="external" target="_blank"> Kiese Laymon on gambling</a>. | Vanity Fair</li>
<li>Patrick McCray wonders: <a href="https://thereader.mitpress.mit.edu/what-is-authorship-when-machines-can-write/" class="external" target="_blank">What is authorship in the age of ChatGPT</a>? | The MIT Press Reader</li>
<li>Good news! Young people <a href="https://www.theverge.com/ai-artificial-intelligence/920401/gen-z-ai" class="external" target="_blank">increasingly hate AI</a>. | The Verge</li>
<li>Kang-Chun Cheng explores <a href="https://www.thedial.world/articles/news/mauritania-chinguetti-libraries" class="external" target="_blank">the fight to preserve ancient literature</a> in Mauritania. | The Dial</li>
<li>Unsurprisingly, <a href="https://www.wired.com/story/maga-is-confused-about-animal-farm/" class="external" target="_blank">the far right doesn&#8217;t understand <i>Animal Farm</i></a>. | Wired</li>
<li>Michele Goodwin considers the misogyny and racism inherent to <a href="https://www.thenation.com/article/society/voting-rights-warning-womens-political-power/" class="external" target="_blank">the gutting of the Voting Rights Act</a>. | The Nation</li>
</ul>
